profile.name: Okta Administrators
profile.description: Okta manages this group, which contains all administrators in your organization.

User Types.description: Okta user profile template with default permission settings

roles.description: An IGA admin role for managing access requests

roles.description: An admin role for managing workflows

Policies.name: Default Policy
Policies.description: The default policy applies in all situations if no other policy applies.

Okta Account Management Policy
Policies.description: This policy defines how users must authenticate for authenticator enrollment, password reset, or unlock account. Password policy rules control whether to enforce this policy for password reset and unlock account.

Policies.name: Entity Risk Policy
Policies.description: Enables entity risk policy evaluation for the org.

Policies.name: Default Policy
Policies.description: The default policy applies in all situations if no other policy applies.

Policies.name: Active Directory Policy
Policies.description: The active directory policy contains settings that apply to users using delegated authentication from active directory integrations.

Policies.name: Default Policy
Policies.description: The default policy applies in all situations if no other policy applies.

Policies.name: Post Auth Policy
Policies.description: Enables post auth policy evaluation for the org.

Authorization Servers.name: default
Authorization Servers.description: Default Authorization Server for your Applications

Org Features.name: Create virtual roles with Collections
Org Features.description: Create virtual roles composed of resources such as apps and entitlements that are assignable to users, request-able by users, and can be reviewed in access certifications

Org Features.name: Workflows Execution Log Streaming
Org Features.description: Enables streaming Workflows execution logs to a downstream endpoint of the customer's choosing

Org Features.name: App settings permissions for custom admin roles
Org Features.description: Super admins can assign permissions for custom admin roles to manage all app settings, or only general app settings.

Org Features.name: Enable custom admin roles for device permissions
Org Features.description: Create custom admin roles with granular permissions for managing devices

Org Features.name: Okta Workflows actions in Access Requests
Org Features.description: Run a delegated flow in Okta Workflows directly from a Request Type.

Org Features.name: Support for POST Request to Authorization Endpoint
Org Features.description: Ability to send user data securely in the request body using POST method support on authorization endpoint

Org Features.name: Workday writeback enhancement
Org Features.description: Use independent Workday API calls to update work and home contacts and avoid unnecessary change requests to Workday. This feature requires Work Contact Change and Home Contact Change business process permissions in Workday.

Org Features.name: Use the default user profile for Org2Org
Org Features.description: Enable using the default user profile only for Org2Org

Org Features.name: Deactivate App Assignments
Org Features.description: When deactivating an Okta user, deactivate the user's individual app assignments instead of suspending them. If a user is reactivated, the individual app assignments don't reactivate.

Org Features.name: Restrict access to the Admin Console
Org Features.description: Grant admin privileges to users without automatically assigning them the Okta Admin Console app.

Org Features.name: Unified look and feel for Okta Dashboard
Org Features.description: Okta first-party app navigation menus and page background have an updated look

Org Features.name: Identity verification with third party identity verification vendors
Org Features.description: Allows you to use third party identity verification vendors (IDVs) to verify the identity of your users when they take certain actions. Verification requirements and identity verification vendors are based on your authentication policies and configurations within the Okta org.

Org Features.name: FIPS compliance
Org Features.description: This feature allows you to configure FIPS compliance on iOS or Android devices that enroll in Okta Verify.

Org Features.name: Enforce MFA for admin-only Identity Governance apps
Org Features.description: This feature makes MFA mandatory to access admin-only Identity Governance apps. In Identity Engine, the Admin App Policy applies to these Identity Governance apps. In Classic Engine, any authentication policy rules that protect these Identity Governance apps are updated from single-factor to 2-factor. If you disable this feature, the changes are not automatically reverted. You must manually edit the rules to allow single-factor access.

Org Features.name: Require phishing-resistant authenticator to enroll additional authenticators
Org Features.description: Users must verify their identity using a phishing-resistant authenticator before enrolling in additional authenticators.

Org Features.name: Google Workspace express setup
Org Features.description: Enables a seamless and efficient integration experience by simplifying SSO setup for the GSuite application

Org Features.name: Import user entitlements from CSV
Org Features.description: Allows admins to upload a CSV file containing users and their entitlements to a governance engine enabled application, resulting in creation and grant of entitlements to the user.

Org Features.name: Certificate-based Authentication for Office 365
Org Features.description: Okta Identity Engine now supports certificate-based authentication for WS-Fed SSO requests. Users can authenticate using smart/PIV cards to seamlessly access their Windows devices and Office 365 applications.

Org Features.name: Include the Sign in with FastPass button when a Smart Card Identity Provider is configured
Org Features.description: Displays both Sign in with FastPass and Sign in with PIV/CAC buttons in the Sign in Widget when a Smart Card Identity Provider is configured.

Org Features.name: Dynamic OS version compliance
Org Features.description: Configure device assurance policies to stay up-to-date with the latest major OS releases and patch updates without manually updating policy.

Org Features.name: Access request conditions and resource catalog
Org Features.description: Streamline configuration of access requests for apps, entitlements, and groups from the app's profile page in the Okta Admin Console. Enable request submission directly integrated with the Okta End User Dashboard.

Org Features.name: Event Hook Filtering
Org Features.description: Allows the addition of filters to Event Hooks to only fire on specific events

Org Features.name: Org2Org Incremental Imports
Org Features.description: Enabling this flag, enables incremental imports for Okta Org2Org

Org Features.name: Biometric user verification in authentication policies
Org Features.description: Configure authentication policies with biometric user verification constraints (no passcode).

Org Features.name: Custom remediation for device assurance
Org Features.description: Display custom remediation instructions to users when authentication fails due to unsuccessful device posture checks with Okta Verify or Chrome Device Trust.

Org Features.name: Force rematch imported users to Okta users
Org Features.description: Force a rematch of all the users brought in by an incremental or full import from a profile source

Org Features.name: End User Settings version 2.0
Org Features.description: Customers are able to update their Account Settings easily with or without logging into the End User Dashboard. End User Settings will be available as its own application that is accessible from End User Dashboard with accessibility and UX improvements.

Org Features.name: Custom languages for Okta Email Templates
Org Features.description: Admins can customize Okta-generated emails in any language

Org Features.name: Enable optional email enrollment for Okta Identity Engine
Org Features.description: Supports optional email authenticator enrollment when Okta Identity Engine is enabled.

Org Features.name: Govern Okta Admin Roles
Org Features.description: Adopt a zero standing privilege model for your org by allowing users to request time-bound access to Okta admin roles and periodically reviewing their admin access.

Org Features.name: Workflows Execution History Inspector
Org Features.description: Adds a panel to the Workflows Execution History page that details card-level performance and usage metrics.

Org Features.name: IDP MyAccount API 2FA If Possible
Org Features.description: The MyAccount API feature provides admins and app developers the ability to support the constraint urn:okta:loa:2fa:any:ifpossible in the acr_values parameter.

Org Features.name: Enable Managed Apple ID federation and provisioning
Org Features.description: This feature enables automatic provisioning of Managed Apple IDs which also provides federated authentication and allows for streamlined access into Apple resources. Okta also enhances the security story by sharing CAEP events through our Shared Signals Framework (SSF) pipeline which allows Apple to take real-time actions on known identity threats.

Org Features.name: Block synced passkeys for FIDO2 (WebAuthn) Authenticators
Org Features.description: Syncable Passkeys are FIDO credentials that are backed up and synchronized across devices.

Org Features.name: OPP Agent with SCIM 2.0 support
Org Features.description: Updated OPP agent with support for Okta's SCIM 2.0 APIs and Entitlement Management for app integrations that have enabled Governance Engine.

Org Features.name: Okta first-party App Switcher
Org Features.description: An admin utility for quick navigation between Okta first-party apps

Org Features.name: Front-channel Single Logout
Org Features.description: SAML and OIDC single logout requests will trigger subsequent logout requests to all other participating apps with active sessions

Org Features.name: Grace period for device assurance
Org Features.description: Configure the device assurance remediation window so users can fix failing conditions to prevent lockout.

Org Features.name: Save password during app sign up
Org Features.description: This feature allows users using the Okta plugin to save usernames and passwords for apps when users sign up for a new account for that app.

Org Features.name: Dynamic resource sets
Org Features.description: Allows admins to exclude resources from a resource set

Org Features.name: Migration Support for Workspace ONE Device Trust for Android and iOS
Org Features.description: This feature provides the capability for migrating existing Workspace ONE Device Trust for mobile configurations into Okta Identity Engine (OIE). This feature must be enabled before running through the self-service upgrade to Okta Identity Engine (OIE).

Org Features.name: Entitlement SAML Assertions and OIDC Claims
Org Features.description: Configure your SAML and OIDC federated app integrations to pass entitlements as custom claims in SAML assertions and OpenID Connect ID tokens.

Org Features.name: Monitor MFA abandonment for authenticator methods
Org Features.description: Allows org admins to monitor MFA abandonment in the system log admin UI using the existing user.authentication.auth_via_mfa event type for one or more authenticator methods used for verification challenges during sign-in flow.

Org Features.name: Okta-to-Okta Claims Sharing
Org Features.description: Enable the admin to configure authentication claims sharing between Okta orgs

Org Features.name: Unified look and feel for Okta Admin Console
Org Features.description: Okta first-party app navigation menus and page background have an updated look

Org Features.name: Enable Custom Admin Roles for Identity Providers
Org Features.description: Create custom admin roles with granular permissions for managing Identity Providers

Org Features.name: Passkeys Autofill
Org Features.description: Enables seamless passwordless sign-ins by allowing users to automatically fill and authenticate with discoverable credentials

Org Features.name: IDP MyAccount Password API
Org Features.description: The MyAccount Password API feature provides admins and app developers access to a user-scoped API endpoint that can create/update/remove password.

Org Features.name: Skip the verify screen and redirect to the IdP authenticator
Org Features.description: This feature allows users to skip the verify step in the Sign-in Widget. They are instead redirected to the IdP authenticator for verification.

Org Features.name: Okta Browser Plugin credential management enhancements
Org Features.description: Users can now click the Okta Browser Plugin's new aura component to fill in the username and password fields when signing in to applications. This provides an alternate method to users for signing in to their apps.

Org Features.name: Same-Device Enrollment for Okta FastPass
Org Features.description: End users will be prompted to enroll into the same device if the org is using Okta FastPass. The enrollment process is more seamless by prompting the user to install and set up Okta Verify with fewer steps.

Org Features.name: Windows Autopilot Enrollment Policy
Org Features.description: IT admins will have the capability to create contextual access policies for Windows Autopilot Enrollment requests. The feature is only supported on Okta Identity Engine (OIE).
